4 I. Thegeneralcourtfindsasfollows:
5 (a) Greek-AmericanswereanimportantpartofNewHampshire'searlyhistory.
6 (b) Greece, officially known as the Hellenic Republic, is one of New Hampshire’s largest
7 tradepartners.
8 (c) New Hampshire should build upon its historic, cultural, and economic ties with the
9 HellenicRepublic.
10 (d) New Hampshire has the highest per capita concentration of Greek Americans in the
11 country.
12 II. The commissioner of the department of business and economic affairs and the secretary of
13 state shall have the authority to establish a New Hampshire-Greece trade council to meet with one or
14 moretrade councilsestablished inthe HellenicRepublic. The purposeof thecouncil shall be to advance
15 bilateral trade and investment between New Hampshire and Greece, initiate joint action on policy issues
16 of mutual interest to New Hampshire and Greece, and promote business and academic exchanges
17 betweenNewHampshireandGreece.
